title: Chicken Parmigiana Casserole
directions: Place your cooked pasta into a 9x13 baking dish. Drizzle olive oil over pasta.
Lay your cubed chicken on top of the pasta.
Sprinkle ¼ cup of panko crumbs over chicken.
Top with mozzarella, panko, and parmesan.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 25 minutes
Uncover for the last five minutes.
ingredients: 3 chicken breasts, cooked and cubed OR 1 package of Costco's Grilled Chicken Breast Strips cut into cubes (this is what I used)
1 jar of your favorite spaghetti sauce, 24 oz.
